@page "/privacy"
@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization
@attribute [AllowAnonymous]

<div class="legal-container">
    <h1 class="legal-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: April 6, 2026</p>

    <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>Who we are</h2>
        <p>
            RSS Reader is an independent, open-source project operated by a single developer. No company or
            third-party team has access to your data. You can
            <a href="https://github.com/brandonchastain/rss-reader">inspect the source code</a> to see exactly
            how your data is handled.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>What we collect</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <strong>A unique account identifier</strong> &mdash; when you sign in with Microsoft, Azure Static
                Web Apps generates an app-specific identifier for your account. This ID cannot be used to identify
                you across other apps or services. <strong>Your email address is never stored.</strong>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Your feed subscriptions</strong> &mdash; the RSS feeds you add to your account.</li>
            <li>
                <strong>Feed content and metadata</strong> &mdash; article text from your feeds, any tags
                you create, which posts you&rsquo;ve saved, and whether you&rsquo;ve read an article (so we can
                show it as read next time you open the app).
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Server logs</strong> &mdash; standard request logs that may include your IP address and
                the pages you visit. These are retained for 30 days and then automatically deleted.
            </li>
        </ul>
        <p>We do not collect analytics, run tracking scripts, or use advertising services of any kind.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>How we use your data</h2>
        <p>Your data is used solely to provide and improve RSS Reader. Specifically:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>To authenticate you and keep your feeds and reading progress in sync.</li>
            <li>To fetch and display articles from the feeds you subscribe to.</li>
            <li>To diagnose errors and maintain the service (via server logs).</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We will never send you emails. Your email address passes through our server during authentication but is not stored or used for any purpose.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>Who can access your data</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>The operator</strong> &mdash; a single developer, for service maintenance and support.</li>
            <li>
                <strong>Microsoft / Azure</strong> &mdash; our cloud infrastructure provider. Your data is
                processed on Azure services under
                <a href="https://privacy.microsoft.com/en-us/privacystatement">Microsoft&rsquo;s Privacy Statement</a>.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Law enforcement</strong> &mdash; only if required by a valid legal process (e.g., a court order).
            </li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>We will never sell your personal data.</strong></p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>Data storage and security</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>All data is stored in encrypted Azure storage in the United States.</li>
            <li>All network traffic between your browser and our servers uses HTTPS.</li>
            <li>The API enforces strict access controls &mdash; you can only access your own data.</li>
            <li>Authentication is handled entirely by Microsoft; your password is never exposed to RSS Reader.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>Data retention and deletion</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Account data</strong> (feeds, articles, reading activity) is kept as long as your account is active.</li>
            <li><strong>Server logs</strong> are automatically deleted after 30 days.</li>
            <li><strong>Backups</strong> are maintained for service reliability and are overwritten on a rolling basis.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            To request deletion of your data, email
            <a href="mailto:privacy@brandonchastain.com">privacy@brandonchastain.com</a>.
            We will process your request within 30 days.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>Your rights</h2>
        <p>Regardless of where you live, you can:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Export</strong> your feed subscriptions at any time via OPML export.</li>
            <li><strong>Request a copy</strong> of all data we hold about you.</li>
            <li><strong>Request deletion</strong> of your account and data.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section legal-gdpr">
        <h2>Additional rights for EU residents (GDPR)</h2>
        <p>If you are in the European Union, you also have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Correct inaccurate personal data.</li>
            <li>Restrict or object to processing of your data.</li>
            <li>Request data portability.</li>
            <li>Lodge a complaint with your local data protection authority.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            <strong>Legal basis:</strong> We process your data to provide the service you signed up for
            (performance of a contract) and to maintain the security and reliability of the service
            (legitimate interest).
        </p>
        <p>
            <strong>International transfers:</strong> Your data is stored in the United States on Microsoft Azure
            infrastructure.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>Cookies and local storage</h2>
        <p>
            RSS Reader does not use tracking cookies. We use a service worker to cache the app for faster loading,
            and browser local storage to remember your session. These are essential for the app to function and
            cannot be used to track you across other websites.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>Children&rsquo;s privacy</h2>
        <p>
            RSS Reader is not intended for children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal data from
            children. If you believe a child has provided us with data, please contact us and we will delete it.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
            We may update this policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated
            &ldquo;Last updated&rdquo; date. Since we don&rsquo;t have your email, we cannot notify you directly
            &mdash; we encourage you to review this page periodically.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>Self-hosting</h2>
        <p>
            RSS Reader is open source. If you prefer complete control over your data, you can
            <a href="https://github.com/brandonchastain/rss-reader/blob/main/README.md">self-host the app</a>
            on your own infrastructure.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
            For any privacy-related questions or requests, email
            <a href="mailto:privacy@brandonchastain.com">privacy@brandonchastain.com</a>.
        </p>
    </section>
</div>
